title: Heroes Speak On Shark Attack In NSW, Beckham Breaks Silence On Family Feud | 10 News+
description: Four separate shark attacks in a matter of hours in NSW has resulted in multiple beach closures and a swimming warning from authorities, with the latest victim being a young man in his 20s who remains in critical condition in Sydney.  Brooklyn Peltz Beckham, the eldest son of David and Victoria Beckham, has broken his silence on the rumours circulating his strained relationship with his family in a powerful statement. title: Bob Katter Unleashes On Migration As Parliament Debates Hate Speech Laws | 10 News+
description: Independent MP Bob Katter has unleashed on migration, singling out Muslims from the Middle East and North Africa as people he wants to bar from Australia. Channel 10 cameraman Ghaith Nadir, a refugee who fled Iraq and has lived in Australia for 15 years, called Katter out during the press conference. It comes as parliament spent all day debating legislation on gun reform and hate speech. title: Jewish Teenagers Targeted With Antisemitic Abuse In Melbourne | 10 News
description: Jewish teenagers have had to run for their lives after two suspects hurled antisemitic abuse from a ute in Melbourne. The five schoolboys were forced to hide as they were stalked and intimidated.

title: Trump Threatens Norwegian Prime Minister After Not Winning Nobel Peace Prize | 10 News
description: Donald Trump has told Norway's Prime Minister he "no longer feels an obligation to think purely of peace" — because he didn't get the Nobel Peace Prize. It came in an extraordinary text message exchange between the pair over Trump's threats to slap tariffs on eight countries he believes are standing in the way of his plan to take over Greenland.
